                                ISIS Ionogram
                     ___________________________________

           ISIS/Alouette Topside Sounder Data Restoration Project

   * Read about the project:
   (1) background information, (2) data selection criteria, (3)
   analog-to-digital (A/D) operation, (4) how to detect erroneous files,
   (5) analysis of digital ionograms and (6) description of the ISIS-2
   sounder modes

   * Retrieve ionogram data from NSSDC's anonymous ftp site.
   Available data sets (click to read format description): (1) binary full
   resolution ionograms: ISIS-1, ISIS-2, (2) binary standard resolution
   ionograms: ISIS-1, ISIS-2, (3) standard ionograms in CDF format
   (skeleton_table: ISIS-1, ISIS-2 (4) header files with information for
   each satellite pass, (5) telemetry-level Pulse Code Modulation (PCM)
   data for all ISIS 2 instruments.

   * Locate data for specified dates, times and other search criteria.

   * View some of the ionograms on NSSDC/SPDF's CDAWeb system.
   A list of available files is given in the CDAWeb ISIS Inventory. First
   time users please read the separate Comments and Viewing Instructions.

   * List of stations for which data are being restored. Location of these
   stations on a world map.

   * Image Gallery

   * Background information about ground stations, their global
   distribution, and data available on 35 mm film.

   * Related software (Fortran):
   Worldmap program for generating orbit parameters; Jackson's program to
   invert the ionogram trace into an electron density profile; An
   interactive tracing and inversion program using IDL ( description of
   program).

   * Extracts from a Spring AGU 1995 computer-interactive poster including
   the conversion of an ionogram trace to an electron density profile
   using a sample ionogram.
